headline: Costco Is One of the Largest Consumer Goods Companies by Market Cap. But Is It a Buy?
summary: Costco is a dominant player in the retail sector, with $62 billion in merchandise sales in the most recent fiscal quarter.  Despite the rise of e-commerce giant Amazon, Costco has continued to grow its membership base.  Investors can start by looking around and identifying companies that they are customers of.
